properties.Name: InsurancePolicyCashReserveValue
properties.Description:
Excess funds that are paid in the early years of a insurance policy create a 'cash value' for the insurance policy.

Ex:
- Policy Cash Value
- Policy Reserve

POLICY CASH VALUE
The cash value is the amount of additional funds paid in the early years of a whole life policy.

POLICY RESERVE
The policy reserve is the amount which when added to the present value of future net premiums will equal the present value of future claims.

Columns.Name: InsurancePolicyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Policy.

Columns.Name: Date
Columns.Description: The date for which the associated cash and reserve values are computed.

Columns.Name: PolicyCashValueAmount
Columns.Description: The cash value is the amount of additional funds paid in the early years of a whole life policy.

Columns.Name: PolicyReserveValueAmount
Columns.Description: The policy reserve is the amount which when added to the present value of future net premiums will equal the present value of future claims.
